DataElement.preferredName: Biospecimen Material Accession Number Text ISO21090.ST.SIMPLE.v1.0
DataElement.preferredDefinition: An alphanumeric identifier (not necessarily unique to the specimen) assigned by a receiving lab to specimens that are received together as a set.

DataElementConcept.preferredDefinition: Any material sample taken from a biological entity for testing, diagnostic, propagation, treatment or research purposes, including a sample obtained from a living organism or taken from the biological object after halting of all its life functions. Biospecimen can contain one or more components including but not limited to cellular molecules, cells, tissues, organs, body fluids, embryos, and body excretory products.:The tangible substance that goes into the makeup of a physical object._A control number unique to an object.  It is used to identify the object among other objects in a collection.:The words of something written.
